<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0010 </DOCNO><TEXT>Sixty-seven patients underwent endoscopic US of the pancreas performedusing a 7.5-MHz transducer mounted on a duodenoscope scanning throughthe GI tract wall. All of the cases represented diagnostic problems resistantto conventional imaging. Small or unusual malignant tumors were correctlydiagnosed in 18 patients. There was one false-positive diagnosis. Allseven islet cell tumors were localized. A definite diagnosis of pancreatitiswas made in 24 of 27 patients, and 13 of 14 patients were confidentlydescribed as normal. In four patients the pancreas could not be visualized.Additional information was obtained in almost all studies. The methodis now their final arbiter of pancreatic problems.</TEXT></DOC>